SIMPLE: recognize
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Recognize
<hw>Rec"og*nize</hw> <pr>(r⟦ecr⟧k"⟦ocr⟧g*n⟦imac⟧z)</pr>, <pos>v.
t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Recognized</conjf>
<pr>(r⟦ecr⟧k"⟦ocr⟧g*n⟦imac⟧zd)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Recognizing</conjf>
<pr>(r⟦ecr⟧k"⟦ocr⟧g*n⟦imac⟧`z⟦icr⟧ng)</pr>.]</vmorph> <ety>[From
<er>Recognizance</er>; see <er>Cognition</er>, and cf.
<er>Reconnoiter</er>.]</ety> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>recognise</asp>.]</altsp> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To know again; to
perceive the identity of, with a person or thing previously known; to
recover or recall knowledge of.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Speak, vassal; <qex>recognize</qex> thy sovereign queen.</q>
<rj><qau>Harte.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To avow knowledge of; to allow that one knows; to
consent to admit, hold, or the like; to admit with a formal
acknowledgment; <as>as, to <ex>recognize</ex> an obligation; to
<ex>recognize</ex> a consul.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To acknowledge acquaintance with, as by salutation,
bowing, or the like.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>To show appreciation of; <as>as, to
<ex>recognize</ex> services by a testimonial</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>To review; to reexamine.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>South.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>6.</sn> <def>To reconnoiter.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>R.
Monro.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- To acknowledge; avow; confess; own; allow;
concede. See <er>Acknowledge</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Recognize</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Recognize
<hw>Rec"og*nize</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>To enter an
obligation of record before a proper tribunal; <as>as, A B
<ex>recognized</ex> in the sum of twenty dollars</as>.</def>
<altsp>[Written also <asp>recognise</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ In legal usage in the United States the second syllable
is often accented.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Recognizee</ent>⟦br⟧
